Welcome to LII
==============



We believe that everyone should be able to read and understand the laws that govern them, without cost. We carry out this vision by:

* Publishing law online, for free.
* Creating materials that help people understand law.
* Exploring new technologies that make it easier for people to find the law.

We hope you'll learn more about us, and help support our work.






What's New?
-----------

### State Regulations

LII now publishes [state regulations for all 50 U.S. states](/regulations). Updates are released quarterly.

### We're hiring!

Keep an eye on this space for new position postings as they become available.

### LII Original Content

* The [Wex Legal Dictionary and Encyclopedia](/wex) has new entries on [statutory interpretation](/wex/statutory_interpretation), [corruption](/wex/corruption), and summaries of recent U.S. Supreme Court decisions.
* The [LII Supreme Court Bulletin](/supct/cert) students prepare and publish [previews of upcoming oral arguments before the U.S. Supreme Court](/supct/oral_arg_previews.php?when=thisterm). Recent previews include:

+ [Trump v. Anderson](https://www.law.cornell.edu/supct/cert/23-719)

* The [Gender Justice Collection](/women-and-justice) now features [a new set of resources on legislation in Ukraine](/women-and-justice/location/ukraine).
### From the Government

* The [Congressional Research Service's U.S. Constitution Annotated](/constitution-conan) now features updates through the most recent U.S. Supreme Court decisions. Updates include:

+ [Modern Doctrine on Appropriate Scrutiny (college admissions)](/constitution-conan/amendment-14/modern-doctrine-on-appropriate-scrutiny)
+ [States and Elections Clause (redistricting)](/constitution-conan/article-1/section-4/clause-1/states-and-elections-clause)
+ [True Threats (social media)](/constitution-conan/amendment-1/true-threats)

* The [U.S. Supreme Court collection](/supremecourt/text): most recent o...

We believe that everyone should be able to read and understand the laws that govern them, without cost. We carry out this vision by:

* Publishing law online, for free.
* Creating materials that help people understand law.
* Exploring new technologies that make it easier for people to find the law.

We hope you'll learn more about us, and help support our work.






What's New?
-----------

### State Regulations

LII now publishes [state regulations for all 50 U.S. states](/regulations). Updates are released quarterly.

### We're hiring!

Keep an eye on this space for new position postings as they become available.

### LII Original Content

* The [Wex Legal Dictionary and Encyclopedia](/wex) has new entries on [statutory interpretation](/wex/statutory_interpretation), [corruption](/wex/corruption), and summaries of recent U.S. Supreme Court decisions.
* The [LII Supreme Court Bulletin](/supct/cert) students prepare and publish [previews of upcoming oral arguments before the U.S. Supreme Court](/supct/oral_arg_previews.php?when=thisterm). Recent previews include:

+ [Trump v. Anderson](https://www.law.cornell.edu/supct/cert/23-719)

* The [Gender Justice Collection](/women-and-justice) now features [a new set of resources on legislation in Ukraine](/women-and-justice/location/ukraine).
### From the Government

* The [Congressional Research Service's U.S. Constitution Annotated](/constitution-conan) now features updates through the most recent U.S. Supreme Court decisions. Updates include:

+ [Modern Doctrine on Appropriate Scrutiny (college admissions)](/constitution-conan/amendment-14/modern-doctrine-on-appropriate-scrutiny)
+ [States and Elections Clause (redistricting)](/constitution-conan/article-1/section-4/clause-1/states-and-elections-clause)
+ [True Threats (social media)](/constitution-conan/amendment-1/true-threats)
